Privacy Policy

Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how TravelKinderdijk (referred to as "we", "us", or "our") handles and protects your personal data when you use our mobile application (the "App"). Specifically, we will explain how we collect, store, and use your personal information, including location data, name, email, and phone number.

1. Data We Collect
We collect and store the following types of personal data when you use our App:

Location Data: We access your location to display it on a map within the App.
Personal Information: We collect your name, email address, and phone number when you create an account. This information is used for the following purposes:
To identify you as the purchaser of digital tours.
To allow you to access previously purchased tours when you log back in.
To contact you if there are any issues related to your account or purchased services.

2. Purpose of Data Collection
We collect and process your personal data for the following purposes:

Location Data: To display your current location on a map, which is essential for the core functionality of the App. This data is not stored on our servers.
Account Information: To manage your account, identify your purchases, and provide customer support. We store your name, email, and phone number securely on our servers.

3. Legal Basis for Processing Personal Data
Under the GDPR, we rely on the following legal bases for processing your personal data:

Consent: We obtain your consent to collect and process your location data.
Performance of a Contract: We process your account information to fulfill our contractual obligations, such as granting you access to purchased tours and providing customer support.
Legitimate Interests: We may process your contact information to communicate with you in the event of issues related to your account or purchases.

4. User Consent
You will be prompted to grant permission for the App to access your location data. You may decline this request, but the map functionality of the App will not work as intended without location access.
By creating an account and using our services, you consent to the collection and processing of your personal information as described in this policy.

5. Your Rights
As a user in the Netherlands or the EU, you have the following rights concerning your personal data under the GDPR:

Access: You have the right to request access to the personal data we hold about you.
Rectification: You can ask us to correct any inaccurate or incomplete data.
Erasure ("Right to be Forgotten"): You can request that we delete your personal data, subject to certain conditions.
Data Portability: You have the right to receive your personal data in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format.
Restriction of Processing: You can request the restriction of processing of your personal data in certain situations.
Objection: You can object to the processing of your personal data on grounds related to your particular situation.
Withdraw Consent: You may withdraw your consent at any time for the processing of your location data by adjusting the settings on your device.
To exercise your rights, contact us at travelkinderdijk@gmail.com.

6. Data Security
We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal data against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, no data transmission over the Internet or electronic storage is completely secure. While we strive to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.

7. Data Retention
We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which we collected it, including to satisfy legal, accounting, or reporting requirements.

8. Third-Party Services
The App may use third-party services (such as map services) to display your location. These services may collect information in accordance with their own privacy policies, which we recommend reviewing. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of third-party services.

9. International Data Transfers
If your personal data is transferred outside the European Economic Area (EEA), we will ensure that appropriate safeguards are in place to protect your data, such as standard contractual clauses approved by the European Commission.

10. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and, where appropriate, notifying you through email or in-App notifications. Please review this Privacy Policy periodically for updates.

11. Contact Us
If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or the handling of your personal data, please contact us at: travelkinderdijk@gmail.com.
